The paper deals with a statistical learning problem (Tukey regression) and proposes dimensionality reduction methods to solve it. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves constructive proofs and algorithmic complexity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also mentions the use of heuristics and empirical results, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
